      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 365: Audio congestion is signaled whenever ponderated loss is above 3%, with no hysteresis or edge detection. As long as loss remains above the threshold this repeatedly calls into video every RTCP interval, leaving throttling policy split between audio and video and making callback users responsible for rate limiting. Prefer firing on threshold crossing or add a clear audio-side cooldown/reset threshold.\\n```suggestion\\nif (pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 lastPondLoss_ \u003c AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD) {\\n    // notify congestion transition\\n}\\nlastPondLoss_ \u003d pondLoss;\\n```",
